			  },
			  "CustomInstructions": "BI Pixie is a groundbreaking solution built to optimize Power BI adoption and trust. It delivers deep insights into user behavior, performance issues, and security risks—empowering Power BI teams in both IT and Line of Business to boost engagement, prevent data leakage, prioritize their Power BI backlog and maximize BI impact and ROI.\n* This Semantic Model stores usage data about users of Power BI reports and semantic models. The data can be in the following 6 dimensions: 1. Adoption; 2. Engagement; 3. User Satisfaction; 4. Business Outcome; 5. Performance; 6. Security. \n* Users can be: 1) Power BI end-users (synonyms: consumers, audience, users, readers). 2) Power BI developers (Synonyms: developers, producers, writers, editors, contributors). In most of the tables of the Semantic Model, when users are involved, they are linked from [User Key] column to Users[User Key]. In most of the cases the users are end-users and not developers, but developers can be end-users as well.\n* When asked about users or specific email address, use the email addresses in 'Users'[User Key] to identify the person and apply a filter on it.\n* When asked about developers, use the Developers table as the dimension for users."
			}
		contentType: json

